# Import libraries and packages
import geopandas as gpd
import folium
from folium import Element
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
In[2]:
# Generate final interactive cluster map
cluster_heatmap_gdf = gpd.read_file("data/final_processed_data/amsterdam_airbnb_tourism_gdf.gpkg")

# 1. Reproject to WGS84 for Leaflet
gdf_wgs = cluster_heatmap_gdf.to_crs(epsg=4326).copy()

# 2. Cluster categories and colors
clusters_to_keep = ["High-High", "Low-Low", "High-Low", "Low-High"]
cluster_palette = {"High-High": "#d7191c","Low-Low":"#2b83ba","High-Low":"#fdae61","Low-High":"#80c4cf"}

# 3. Helper to build style functions for each attribute
def make_style_function(attribute):
    def style_function(feature):
        cluster = feature["properties"].get(attribute)
        color = cluster_palette.get(cluster, "#cccccc")  # grey for anything unexpected
        return {
            "fillColor": color,"color": "white","weight": 0.25,"fillOpacity": 0.6 if cluster in clusters_to_keep else 0.0}
    return style_function

# 4. Map center (rough centroid of all polygons)
gdf_wgs_centroid = gdf_wgs.geometry.unary_union.centroid
center_lat, center_lon = gdf_wgs_centroid.y, gdf_wgs_centroid.x

# 5. Base maps (only one shows at a time; controlled by LayerControl)
final_map = folium.Map(location=[center_lat, center_lon], zoom_start=12, tiles=None)
folium.TileLayer('NL Maps Luchtfoto',name='nlmaps.luchtfoto', show=True).add_to(final_map)
folium.TileLayer('CartoDB DarkMatter',name='CartoDB.DarkMatter', show=False).add_to(final_map)
folium.TileLayer('CartoDB Positron',name='CartoDB.positron', show=False).add_to(final_map)
folium.TileLayer('OpenStreetMap',name='OSM.Mapnik', show=False).add_to(final_map)

# 6. Define the cluster layers we want to toggle
layers = [("Airbnb prices","cluster_airbnbprices"),("Airbnb locations","cluster_airbnbs"),("Tourism POI locations","cluster_pois"),("Monument locations","cluster_monuments")]
# keep only rows with valid cluster labels
for layer_name, attribute in layers:
    layer_gdf = gdf_wgs[gdf_wgs[attribute].isin(clusters_to_keep)].copy()
    fg = folium.FeatureGroup(name=layer_name, show=(attribute == "cluster_airbnbprices"))
    folium.GeoJson(data=layer_gdf,style_function=make_style_function(attribute),tooltip=folium.GeoJsonTooltip(fields=["Buurt","cluster_airbnbprices","cluster_airbnbs","cluster_pois","cluster_monuments"],aliases=["Neighborhood:","Airbnb Price cluster:","Airbnb Locations cluster:","Tourism POIs cluster:","Monuments cluster:"],localize=True),name=layer_name).add_to(fg)
    fg.add_to(final_map)
# Add layer control to toggle between the cluster layers
folium.LayerControl(collapsed=False).add_to(final_map)

# 7. Add title and legend
title_html = """<div style="position:fixed; top:10px; left:50%; transform:translateX(-50%); z-index:9999; background-color:white; padding:6px 12px; border:1px solid #ccc; border-radius:4px; font-size:14px;"><b>Local Indicators of Spatial Association (LISA) Clusters - Airbnbs & Tourism in Amsterdam</b></div>"""
legend_html = """<div style="position:fixed; bottom:30px; right:10px; z-index:9999; background-color:white; padding:8px 10px; border:1px solid #ccc; border-radius:4px; font-size:12px;"><b>LISA clusters</b><br><i style="background:#d7191c; width:12px; height:12px; float:left; margin-right:6px; opacity:0.7;"></i>High-value cluster<br><i style="background:#2b83ba; width:12px; height:12px; float:left; margin-right:6px; opacity:0.7;"></i>Low-value cluster<br><i style="background:#fdae61; width:12px; height:12px; float:left; margin-right:6px; opacity:0.7;"></i>High-value outlier<br><i style="background:#80c4cf; width:12px; height:12px; float:left; margin-right:6px; opacity:0.7;"></i>Low-value outlier<br></div>"""
final_map.get_root().html.add_child(Element(title_html))
final_map.get_root().html.add_child(Element(legend_html))

# 8. Export and display
final_map.save("LISA_interactive_map.html")
final_map
